{"lemma":"سُخْرَةٌ","slug":"سُخْرَةٌ","root":"س.خ.ر","root_slug":"س-خ-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/س-خ-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n19195"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8F%D8%AE%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"corvee"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"laughingstock"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"ridiculer"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19195","headword_ar":"سُخْرَةٌ","root":"sxr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who is mocked at, scoffed at, laughed at, derided,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ridiculed; a laughingstock;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sixoriY~N","text_ar":"سِخْرِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suxoriY~N","text_ar":"سُخْرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Az, A;) which are used as sing., as in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ait~axa*uwhu","text_ar":"اِتَّخَذُوهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suiHoriy~FA","text_ar":"سُِحْرِيًّا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they made him a laughingstock;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A;) and as pl., as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo laka suixoriY~N","text_ar":"هُمْ لَكَ سُِخْرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suixoriy~apN","text_ar":"سُِخْرِيَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", the former being masc. and the latter fem.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they are to thee laughingstocks;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the former occurring in the Kur [see xxiii. 112, and xxxviii. 63, and xliii. 31,] with damm and with kesr accord. to different readings. (Az, TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who is constrained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"compelled, to do what he does not desire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to work, without recompense,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wages;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, * Mgh, * Msb, * K, * TA;) applied to a servant, (JK, S, Msb,) and to a beast; (JK, Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suxoriY~N","text_ar":"سُخْرِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sixoriY~N","text_ar":"سِخْرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K) or the former of these, only, is used in this sense; and the latter, and sometimes the former also, in the sense immediately preceding: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suxorapN","text_ar":"سُخْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used as a pl., (JK, A,) as in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`w^ulaA='i suxorapN lils~uloTaAni","text_ar":"هٰوُلَا=ءِ سُخْرَةٌ لِلسُّلْطَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"these are persons made use of without compensation for the Sultán:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, * A:) it also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who employs any person,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that he has subjected,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"compelled to obey him, without recompense,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wages:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) [or this is a mistake, and the correct signification is]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who is so employed by him who has subjected him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b3-  It is also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasoxiyrN","text_ar":"تَسْخِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[inf. n. of 2]. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"smE","text_ar":"سمع"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["JK","S","Msb","K","TA","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}